b'[<p><i><b>UFC 49: Unfinished Business</b></i> was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held by the <a href="/wiki/Ultimate_Fighting_Championship" title="Ultimate Fighting Championship">Ultimate Fighting Championship</a> on August 21, 2004, at the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/MGM_Grand_Arena" title="MGM Grand Arena">MGM Grand Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Las_Vegas,_Nevada" title="Las Vegas, Nevada">Las Vegas, Nevada</a>.  The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Pay-per-view" title="Pay-per-view">pay-per-view</a> in the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a>, and later released on <a href="/wiki/DVD" title="DVD">DVD</a>.\n</p>, <p>It featured the anticipated rubber match between Light Heavyweight Champion <a href="/wiki/Vitor_Belfort" title="Vitor Belfort">Vitor Belfort</a> and <a href="/wiki/Randy_Couture" title="Randy Couture">Randy Couture</a>, following a disappointing doctor\'s stoppage in their last encounter at <i><a href="/wiki/UFC_46" title="UFC 46">UFC 46</a></i>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>This event featured the last UFC fight in the lightweight division until <a href="/wiki/UFC_58" title="UFC 58">UFC 58</a> on March 4, 2006.\n</p>]'